Dev Log - 2026-05-01

**Summary**

contract hardening day

Today was mostly about tightening the Codex runner and the beta handoff path so the system is easier to execute, easier to reason about, and harder to misuse. The center of gravity was not new surface area; it was making the existing execution path more governed and more legible.

The work also removed a bit of ambiguity from the beta handoff flow. One commit finalized the verifier, another removed a graph health gate that was no longer serving the handoff contract. Taken together, the day was about reducing false dependencies and making the runner and release path more explicit about what they do and do not require.

**What I completed**

**Codex runner and TUI refinement**

- Refined the codex_runner package and its TUI layer in codex_runner/runner.py, codex_runner/tui_app.py, codex_runner/tui_commands.py, and codex_runner/tui_state.py.
